                                    [vidtitel] => «Until Next Time»
                                    [viddate] => 2010, Dan Green
                                    [vidtext] => 3’20’’, SD video, ed. 1<br> <br> ‘Until Next Time’ appears to be a tender letter to a lover being left behind. The journey has no specified beginning or end and is through virgin snow which, whilst beautiful is also inherently dangerous and seen through the impenetrable window of a train. The narrators memory of what appears to be a life-changing event is somehow altered and made more fantastical through the human process of re-remembering only the good parts of each occurrence. His fondness for the undescribed lover is apparent, as his knowledge that the journey through life and the sum of all experiences is key to understanding a person’s development and identity.
